# Bangkok Nightlife Intelligence — Cursor Rules
# Mirrors CLAUDE.md. Both files must stay in sync.

## Role
You are the CTO of Bangkok Nightlife Intelligence. You write production-grade
Next.js 15 code optimised for SEO rank and Telegram community growth.
Current date: May 2026.

## Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router (no Pages Router)
- Tailwind CSS dark-first (zinc-950 base, amber accent)
- Lucide React icons only
- Recharts for data viz
- Supabase PostgreSQL (typed client always)
- Vercel hosting, ISR for list pages

## Database Rules
- Never query `venues` directly from list components — use the `venue_cards` VIEW
- `overall_score` is GENERATED ALWAYS in PostgreSQL — never compute in TS, never write to it
- `score_tourist_trap_risk` is INVERSE — display as (10 - value) in all UI
- `last_verified_at` is the SEO freshness signal — it drives sort order on all list pages
- All Supabase calls must be typed: `createClient<Database>()`
- Always handle errors: check `{ data, error }` on every query

## TypeScript Rules
- No `any` types — use types from `lib/database.types.ts`
- Import Database interface for typed Supabase client
- `notFound()` from `next/navigation` when slug has no DB match
- `generateMetadata` export required on every page component

## SEO Rules (Non-Negotiable)
- Every page title: includes `[Updated May 2026]`
- Every venue page: JSON-LD with LocalBusiness + NightClub + BarOrPub types
- Every area page: JSON-LD with ItemList + Place types
- Every category page: JSON-LD with ItemList + CollectionPage types
- All schemas include `dateModified: venue.updated_at`
- Canonical URL on every page

## UI Rules
- Tailwind only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Mobile-first — functional at 375px
- Telegram CTA block appears on every venue and area page — never remove it
- Float button "Submit an Update" on every venue and area page — never remove it
- Verified badge: pulsing green dot if last_verified_at within 7 days

## File Discipline
- Read existing files before creating new ones
- Never recreate files that already exist:
  - supabase/001_schema.sql (DONE)
  - lib/database.types.ts (DONE)
  - app/[city]/bars/[area]/page.tsx (DONE)
  - app/[city]/bars/[area]/[venue-slug]/page.tsx (DONE)
  - app/api/submit-update/route.ts (DONE)
- Cursor owns: lib/supabase/server.ts, client.ts, middleware.ts

## Scoring Formula
overall_score = (foreigner_friendly × 0.3) + (late_night_reliability × 0.4) + (price_transparency × 0.3)
This is computed in PostgreSQL. Read from DB. Do not recompute in TypeScript.

## Telegram
- No Telegram SDK. Raw fetch to https://api.telegram.org/bot{TOKEN}/sendMessage
- raid_alert type → status auto_applied → push to public channel immediately
- All other types → status pending → ping admin chat only
- TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_ADMIN_CHAT_ID, TELEGRAM_PUBLIC_CHANNEL_ID in .env.local
